-- Ontario Teachers' Fund Wants $1.5 Billion for Maple Leaf Stake, Globe Says
-- B y   A l a n   P u r k i s s
-- 2010-12-03T09:55:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-03/ontario-fund-wants-1-5-billion-for-maple-leaf-stake-globe-says.html
The Ontario Teachers’ Pension Plan
wants $1.5 billion for its 66 percent stake in Maple Leaf Sports
& Entertainment Ltd., the Globe & Mail reported, citing
unidentified people with knowledge of the matter.  While the pension plan isn’t actively seeking buyers, it’s
open to offers and has been for some years, the newspaper said.  Maple Leaf owns the Toronto Maple Leafs hockey team and the
Raptors basketball club.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
